We will use "group/version" frequently and it's not a simple `group+"/"+version` because we have "v1" as a special case. I think it's inefficient to call a function to concatenate the group with version. How about we keep all three in the struct?

```
type TestGroup struct {
    Group string
    Version string
    // in the format of "group/version"
    GroupVersionUnderTest string
}
```

